    slug: "fazail-e-quran-majeed",
    description: `Fazail e Quran Majeed is an Urdu-language book dedicated to presenting the virtues, excellences, and blessings of the Holy Quran as described in the Quran itself and in the authentic hadith of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). The book compiles and organizes the extensive body of textual evidence that highlights the unique status of the Quran as the final revelation from Allah, the greatest miracle bestowed upon Prophet Muhammad, the source of all guidance for humanity, and the means through which believers can attain success in both this world and the Hereafter. The title "Quran Majeed" — meaning the Noble or Glorious Quran — reflects the reverence with which the book approaches its subject, presenting the Quran as a divine treasure whose benefits and blessings are beyond full enumeration.

The book is structured around specific categories of virtues associated with the Quran. It covers the rewards promised for reciting the Quran, including the hadith stating that each letter of the Quran earns ten rewards and that the status of a believer is raised in proportion to the amount of Quran they have memorized and recited. It discusses the special merits of particular surahs, such as Surah Al-Fatiha (the greatest surah), Surah Al-Baqarah and Ayatul Kursi (which protect from evil), the last two surahs (Al-Falaq and An-Nas, which serve as a cure and protection), and Surah Al-Mulk (which intercedes for its reader). The book also addresses the virtues of reflecting upon and understanding the Quran, the importance of acting upon its teachings, the blessings of teaching the Quran to others, the status of the hafiz (one who has memorized the entire Quran), and the connection between the Quran and the angels who descend to listen to its recitation.

Beyond the enumeration of virtues, Fazail e Quran Majeed also addresses the practical aspects of engaging with the Quran in daily life. It discusses the etiquettes of handling, reciting, and storing the Quran, the recommended times and conditions for recitation, the practice of completing a khatm (full reading) of the Quran and the rewards associated with it, and the importance of maintaining a daily recitation habit. The book warns against neglecting the Quran, citing the stern warnings in the Quran and hadith about those who abandon Allah's book after it has come to them. The Urdu language used is accessible and devotional in tone, making the book suitable for a wide audience that includes students of Islamic studies, teachers at Quran schools, imams and khateebs who prepare sermons about the Quran, and general Muslims who want to deepen their appreciation for the book that is the foundation of their faith. The compilation format makes it easy to reference specific topics and to use selected passages for study circles, classroom instruction, or personal reflection.`,
